column5: Welcome Nikki and great to meet you on Sunday. You rassled those big cats like a champ! Would have liked to see you smack Jer with a big channel cat! (Kidding... Well sort of...!)  Looking forward to seeing your great catches, and Jeremy's photography  I'll get you officially added to the team 6 roster when I do the next update shortly.  Pete
An honest and humorous intro. Welcome to OFC
Welcome Nikki  LMBO

Hey all! Just wanted to quickly introduce myself. Name is Nikki. I've been directed to the forums by my partner (jeremy84) so he can steal my inches for the tournament...I mean, draft me into their team. This year will be my second season casting. I prefer spinnerbait, currently using a 5'2" ugly stick with an Abu Garcia Cardinal reel as my go to and yes I do hook my own worms, although I won't take the fish off the hook if I'm worried I'll pull a chunk out of 'em. I think largemouth are my favourite so far because of their markings, although I'm only 10 species in. This year I want to go for carp, sheepshead and nab a musky.  Off the water I'm a pretty dorky layabout. I work for a bank and spend a lot of free time on the couch binge watching Netflix, especially in winter. I love food, I read constantly, I'm a console gamer (currently PS3, preference to RPGs and third person adventure). I have two cats and sometimes foster. I'm a fairly friendly gal, so say hi if there's anything you wanna know about me.  Here are some pics of some of my favourite catches

We have been together for 24 years. Good luck.
